
                        Section 2 - Notes
                        EXPOSE Instruction
                   Nginix Server Standard Banner

1.  Run detached webserver container. 
    Map port 80 in container to port 5678 on host.

    $ docker run -d --name webserver -p 5678:80 nginx

2.  Show ports for webserver container.

    $ docker port webserver
    80/tcp -> 0.0.0.0:5678

3.  Show HTML with curl localhost and port.

    $ curl localhost:5678
    <!DOCTYPE html>
    <html>
    <head>
    <title>Welcome to nginx!</title>
    . . .
    </html>

4.  Show in browser with URL.

    http://localhost:5678

5.  Cleanup

    $ docker stop webserver
    $ docker container prune -f
